riod in which women's reproductive lives are imperiled, Reproductive Justice provides an essential guide to understanding and mobilizing around women's human rights in the twenty-first century.   Reproductive Justice: A New Vision for the Twenty-First Century publishes works that explore the contours and content of reproductive justice. The series will include primers intended for students and those new to reproductive justice as well as books of original research that will further knowledge and impact society. Learn more at www.ucpress.edu/go/reproductivejustice.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 16. Mai 2019) 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Women's Studies.2bisacsh1 aSolinger, Rickie, eauthor.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook-Package 2016-2018z978311063539308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook-Package 2017z978311066755408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUCal Press eBook Package Frontlist 2017-2018z978311065859040uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520963207423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780520963207.jpg  a978-3-11-063539-3  UC Press eBook-Package 2016-2018  a978-3-11-065859-0  UCal Press eBook Package Frontlist 2017-2018  a978-3-11-066755-4  UC Press eBook-Package 2017  aGBV-deGruyter-alles